programme.desc: From a screenplay by Shia LaBeouf, based on his own experiences, brings to life a young actor's stormy childhood and early adult years as he struggles to reconcile with his father.

programme.title: Maria Full of Grace
programme.desc: A pregnant Colombian teenager becomes a drug mule to make some desperately needed money for her family.

programme.title: Hereafter
programme.desc: George is a blue-collar American who has a special connection to the afterlife. On the other side of the world, Marie, a French journalist, has a near-death experience that shakes her reality. When Marcus, a London schoolboy, loses the person closest to him, he desperately needs answers. Each on a path in search of the truth, their lives will intersect, forever changed by what they believe might - or must - exist in the Hereafter.

programme.title: O Brother, Where Art Thou?
programme.desc: Disenchanted with the daily drudge of crushing rocks on a prison farm in Mississippi, the dapper, silver-tongued Ulysses Everett McGill busts loose. Except he's still shackled to his two chain-mates from the chain gang: bad-tempered Pete and sweet, dim-witted Delmar. With nothing to lose and buried loot to regain - before it's lost forever in a flood - the three embark on the adventure of a lifetime in this hilarious, offbeat road picture. Populated with strange characters, including a blind prophet, sexy sirens and a one-eyed Bible salesman, it's an odyssey filled with chases, close calls, near misses, and betrayal that will leave you laughing at every outrageous and surprising twist and turn.

programme.title: The Talented Mr. Ripley
programme.desc: Tom, a calculating young man, believes it's better to be a fake somebody than a real nobody. Opportunity knocks in the form of a wealthy US shipbuilder who hires Tom to travel to Italy to bring back his playboy son, Dickie. Ripley worms his way into the idyllic lives of Dickie and his girlfriend, plunging into a daring scheme of duplicity, lies and murder.

programme.title: Bad Education
programme.desc: This fact-based dark comedy tells the story of the Long Island school supervisors behind the largest public school embezzlement scandal in American history.

programme.title: Inside Man
programme.desc: A tough cop, a clever bank robber, and a powerbroker fuel a dangerous game of cat-and-mouse full of hidden agendas and explosive surprises.

programme.title: The Sunset Limited
programme.desc: Nihilistic professor White's attempt to commit suicide by jumping in front of a train is thwarted by Black. Locked in a philosophical debate, Black tries to save him from despair.

programme.title: The Firm
programme.desc: A young gun takes a job in a law firm with connections to the Mafia and is soon caught up in blackmail.

programme.title: Ladies in Black
programme.desc: Adapted from the bestselling novel by Madeleine St John, Ladies In Black is an alluring and tender-hearted comedy drama about the lives of a group of department store employees in 1959 Sydney.

programme.title: Hanna
programme.desc: Hanna is a teenage girl. Uniquely, she has the strength, the stamina, and the smarts of a soldier; these come from being raised by her father, an ex-CIA man, in the wilds of Finland. Living a life unlike any other teenager, her upbringing and training have been one and the same, all geared to making her the perfect assassin. The turning point in her adolescence is a sharp one; sent into the world by her father on a mission, Hanna journeys stealthily across Europe while eluding agents dispatched after her by a ruthless intelligence operative with secrets of her own. As she nears her ultimate target, Hanna faces startling revelations about her existence and unexpected questions about her humanity.

programme.title: Victoria & Abdul
programme.desc: The extraordinary true story of the amazing and unlikely friendship between Queen Victoria and a clerk, Abdul Karim, who becomes her teacher, spiritual adviser, and devoted friend.

programme.title: Everybody's Fine
programme.desc: Frank is a recently retired widower who has planned his first family get-together since his wife's death, and is disappointed when his adult children all cancel on him. Accordingly, and against his doctor's advice, Frank sets out on a cross-country road trip via bus and train to pay surprise visits to all of them.

programme.title: Bad Education
programme.desc: This fact-based dark comedy tells the story of the Long Island school supervisors behind the largest public school embezzlement scandal in American history.

programme.title: The Talented Mr. Ripley
programme.desc: Tom, a calculating young man, believes it's better to be a fake somebody than a real nobody. Opportunity knocks in the form of a wealthy US shipbuilder who hires Tom to travel to Italy to bring back his playboy son, Dickie. Ripley worms his way into the idyllic lives of Dickie and his girlfriend, plunging into a daring scheme of duplicity, lies and murder.

programme.title: Donnie Brasco
programme.desc: An FBI undercover agent infiltrates the mob and finds himself identifying more with the mafia life to the expense of his regular one.

programme.title: Green Zone
programme.desc: Discovering covert and faulty intelligence causes a US Army officer to go rogue as he hunts for weapons of mass destruction in an unstable region.

programme.title: Apollo 13
programme.desc: Stranded 205,000 miles from Earth in a crippled spacecraft, astronauts Jim Lovell, Fred Haise and Jack Swigert fight a desperate battle to survive. Meanwhile, at Mission Control, astronaut Ken Mattingly, flight director Gene Kranz and a heroic ground crew race against time - and the odds - to bring them home.

programme.title: The Aviator
programme.desc: Howard Hughes was a wily industrialist, glamorous movie producer and unstoppable American innovator - but thought of himself first and foremost as an aviator. This spectacular epic focuses on the most prolific period in the life of Hughes: the mid-1920s through the 1940s. It was a time of brilliant aeronautical invention, turbulent love affairs and savage corporate battles. Prepare yourself for the ride of a visionary lifetime.

programme.title: Life Support
programme.desc: In her youth, Ana made choices that wrecked her life and splintered her family. Ana is trying to purge the demons of her past by giving something back to her community. But as she learns, winning over strangers is a lot easier than winning back your family.

programme.title: Elephant
programme.desc: Several ordinary high school students go through their daily routine as two others prepare to gun down as many peers as possible. Partly based on the Columbine High massacre.

programme.title: White Mile
programme.desc: An ad executive faces a crisis of conscience when the white-water rafting trip his boss organised ends in tragedy.

programme.title: Mulholland Drive
programme.desc: A mind-altering journey to the dark heart of the American dream, where sinister forces lurk beneath every surface. Naive ingenue Betty Elms has comes to Hollywood to seek fame and fortune - but she finds something much more disturbing waiting in her apartment - a mysterious woman whose only memory is that someone is trying to kill her. What begins as a simple premise unfolds into a shattering hallucinogenic vision of what it takes to make it in Hollywood. No one comes out with the soul intact.

programme.title: True Grit
programme.desc: Mattie Ross is determined to avenge her father's blood by capturing Tom Chaney, the man who shot and killed him for two pieces of gold. Just 14, she enlists the help of Rooster Cogburn, a one-eyed, trigger-happy US Marshal with an affinity for drinking, and hardened Texas Ranger LaBoeuf to track the fleeing Chaney. Despite their differences, their ruthless determination leads them on a perilous adventure that can only have one outcome: retribution.

programme.title: Real Women Have Curves
programme.desc: In East Los Angeles, an 18-year-old struggles between her ambitions of going to college and the desires of her domineering mother for her to get married, have children, and oversee the small, rundown family-owned textile factory.

programme.title: The Shawshank Redemption
programme.desc: An extraordinary tale of hope, friendship and survival inside a maximum security prison. Andy Dufresne is a soft-spoken, respected Maine banker who is convicted for the murders of his unfaithful wife and her lover. He receives a double-life sentence and is shipped off to Shawshank State Prison, Maine's toughest maximum security penitentiary. Despised at first by the other inmates because of his introverted manner, he slowly forges an unlikely friendship with the prison fixer, Red, and they both learn that hope is the ultimate means of survival.

programme.title: The Blind Side
programme.desc: Michael Oher knows little about family. Less about football. What the homeless teen knows are the streets and projects of Memphis. Well-to-do Leigh Anne Tuohy knows little about his world. Yet when she and Michael meet, he's found a home. And the Tuohys have found something just as life-changing, a beloved new son and brother. This real-life story of family and of Michael's growth into a blue-chip football star will have you cheering with its mix of gridiron action and heartwarming emotion. Share the remarkable journey of the college all-American and first-round NFL draft pick who was a winner before he ever stepped onto the playing field.

programme.title: Almost Famous
programme.desc: A high-school boy in the early 1970s is given the chance to write a story for Rolling Stone magazine about an up-and-coming rock band as he accompanies them on their concert tour.

programme.title: Twister
programme.desc: Thrill-seeking meteorologists are chasing the most destructive tornado in 50 years.

programme.title: The Karate Kid (1984)
programme.desc: A new kid in town who is picked on by bullies learns karate and eastern philosophy from Mr Miyagi, and learns how to fight back.

programme.title: Back to the Future
programme.desc: Marty McFly, a typical American teenager of the 1980s, is accidentally sent back to 1955 in a plutonium-powered DeLorean time machine, invented by a slightly mad scientist. During his often hysterical but amazing trip back in time, Marty must make certain his teenage parents-to-be meet and fall in love so that he can get back to the future.

programme.title: Out of Africa
programme.desc: Karen Blixen establishes a plantation in Africa. Meeting her true love, Denys, allows her to rethink her priorities in the midst of this vast land.

programme.title: The Breakfast Club
programme.desc: When Saturday detention started, they were the Jock, the Princess, the Brain, the Criminal, and the Basket Case, but by that afternoon they had become closer than any of them could have imagined.

programme.title: Brewster's Millions
programme.desc: Montgomery Brewster is a minor league baseball pitcher who discovers he has to blow $30 million in 30 days as a condition to inherit a much greater fortune. Here's the catch, he will forfeit everything if he reveals to a soul the real reason he seems to be throwing away all that cash. With the help of his pal Spike they set off on a frantic spending spree the likes of which would bring any self-respecting accountant to his knees.

programme.title: Second Civil War
programme.desc: The media, the White House and the world watch as Idaho's Governor closes borders to a planeload of Pakistani refugees.

programme.title: Quadrophenia
programme.desc: Two rival youth cults emerge, the mods and the rockers with consequences. For Jimmy and his sharp-suited, pill-popping, being a mod is a way of life, it's their generation.

programme.title: El Diablo
programme.desc: In this rowdy Western, when a mild-mannered schoolteacher who can't ride or shoot faces up to a notorious outlaw, he enlists the aid of a tough gunslinger.

programme.title: Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves
programme.desc: After being captured by Turks during the Crusades, Robin of Locksley and a Moor, Azeem, escape back to England where Azeem vows to remain until he repays Robin for saving his life. Meanwhile, Robin's father has been murdered by the Sheriff of Nottingham and when Robin returns home he vows to avenge his father's death. Even though Marian, his childhood friend, cannot help him, he escapes to the Forest of Sherwood where he joins a band of exiled villagers and becomes their leader. With their help he attempts to cleanse the land of the evil that the Sheriff has spread.

programme.title: Death Becomes Her
programme.desc: Two Hollywood divas' surgery-enhanced rivalry goes beyond the grave.

programme.title: Total Recall (1990)
programme.desc: Douglas Quaid/Hauser is haunted each night by a dream that he is on Mars looking for beautiful Melina. He goes against his wife Lori's wishes and visits the Recall laboratories. They claim that they can help make his dream a reality by offering him an adventurous trip in his mind with a powerful hallucinogenic drug. But the experience has unexpected consequences, the drug awakens a memory that was erased from Quaid's mind. In fact he is not Quaid, he is a dangerous terrorist fighting against a Martian despot, Lori is not his wife she is an enemy agent and the red planet is at the heart of a terrifying plot. Pitiless killers relentlessly chase Quaid and he goes to Mars where other memories and other dangers await him, including Melina, the woman of his dreams and he makes an incredible discovery about his own identity.

programme.title: The Frighteners
programme.desc: A small-town 'ghostbuster' is in league with the very spirits he's supposed to be exorcising. The scam works well until a powerful spirit goes on a murderous rampage, forcing Frank to find a way to stop the diabolical ghoul in this special-effects-packed supernatural chiller that's so fiendishly entertaining, it's frightening!

programme.title: Ghostbusters
programme.desc: A trio of university parapsychologists lose their research grant and decide to open their own business, Ghostbusters, and almost at once are summoned to investigate the strange happenings in a Central Park West apartment. What they discover is that all Manhattan is being besieged by otherworldly demons.

programme.title: Planes, Trains & Automobiles
programme.desc: Businessman Neal is dying to get home for Thanksgiving and loud-mouthed Del, a shower curtain ring salesman is driving him nuts. Will they reach Chicago without killing each other?

programme.title: Lawrence of Arabia
programme.desc: When T.E. Lawrence was attached to the British general staff in Arabia, he inspired the feuding Arabian chieftains to rebel against the Turks, leading to the birth of the Arabian kingdom.

programme.title: Batman (1989)
programme.desc: After witnessing the brutal murder of his parents as a child, millionaire philanthropist Bruce Wayne pledges his life to fighting crime disguised as Batman. His long-time nemesis, The Joker, has sinister plans for the citizens of Gotham City. The Joker's greed is matched by his obsession with photojournalist Vicki Vale. Batman is there to counter the Joker's every move. With the fate of Gotham and Vicki in the balance, will good or evil prevail?

programme.title: Bram Stoker's Dracula
programme.desc: Dracula, the vampire doomed as a creature of the night after forsaking God, is aroused by the image of a woman resembling his lost love.

programme.title: The Karate Kid (1984)
programme.desc: A new kid in town who is picked on by bullies learns karate and eastern philosophy from Mr Miyagi, and learns how to fight back.

programme.title: Back To The Future II
programme.desc: Marty McFly returns, this time travelling forward to 2015 with wacky Doc Brown to save his kids. Their crazy time-travels have a mind-bending effect on history.

programme.title: Tommy Boy
programme.desc: Tommy Callahan graduates after seven years of college with a D+ and returns to his home town to learn the family business where his dad Big Tom is extremely proud. But Tommy's plans are turned upside down when Big Tom marries Bo Derek and he finds himself confronted with buyout attempts by his stepbrother Paul. To help him save the plant, Tommy enlists the help of his father's aid. Richard Hayden is the most efficient but obnoxious man in the company. Together they hit the road and the road hits back!

programme.title: Twins
programme.desc: An ambitious genetic experiment takes the wrong turn when two twins - who look nothing alike - are born and then separated. Years later, the unlikely siblings meet: Julius, a highly educated but sheltered giant with a big heart, and Vincent, a pint-sized hustler with an insatiable lust for women and money. With girlfriends in tow and a hitman on their tail, the new-found brothers set off on a wild, cross-country misadventure to find their mother - but end up finding out more about themselves.

programme.title: Planes, Trains & Automobiles
programme.desc: Businessman Neal is dying to get home for Thanksgiving and loud-mouthed Del, a shower curtain ring salesman is driving him nuts. Will they reach Chicago without killing each other?

programme.title: Tango & Cash
programme.desc: Two narcotics detectives can't stand each other. When a crime lord frames them for murder, they have to buddy up to clear their names and put him away.

programme.title: Caddyshack
programme.desc: While caddying at a snooty country club, ambitious young Danny goes for a college scholarship. But first he has to impress elitist Judge Smails and win the big golf tournament. Meanwhile, a crude construction tycoon goes to extremes to be accepted into the exclusive club, and a psychotic groundskeeper stalks a rampaging gopher.

programme.title: The Blues Brothers
programme.desc: After the release of Jake Blues from prison, he and brother Elwood go to visit the orphanage where they were raised by nuns. They learn that the church stopped its support and will sell the place unless the tax on the property is paid within 11 days. The brothers decide to raise the money by putting their blues band back together and staging a big gig. They may be on a 'mission from God' but they're making enemies everywhere they go.

programme.title: The Meaning of Life
programme.desc: The Monty Python team tackle this weighty subject in a series of sketches involving body parts, religion, the wonders of war, the miracle of birth, and a preview of what awaits in heaven.

programme.title: National Lampoon's Animal House
programme.desc: This raunchy, screwball comedy offers a relentless spoof of 1960s college life by following the hilarious adventures of the Delta fraternity.

programme.title: Montana
programme.desc: Ranchers and their children are divided over whether to sell their land.

programme.title: Star Trek: The Motion Picture
programme.desc: A big giant head of alien power is heading toward earth, destroying everything in its path. Who you gonna call? Not that whippersnapper Will Decker, that's for sure - even if he is the new commander of a revamped Enterprise. One look at that great ball of fire convinces Captain Kirk that only one man can save the world.

programme.title: Field of Dreams
programme.desc: After a voice tells a farmer to put a baseball diamond in his cornfield, the ghosts of famous players begin to appear on it.

programme.title: Primal Fear
programme.desc: Guilty? Innocent? Those questions aren't for a high powered Chicago attorney to decide. His job is to defend - especially if a case will put his name in the headlines and further his career. When Vail hears that penniless altar boy is accused of murdering the local archbishop, he snaps up the case, eager for the media spotlight. Little does he know he will uncover a viper's nest of corruption, pit him against a prosecutor who's his ex-lover, and test all of his skill, judgement and even his win at any cost attitude.

programme.title: Frantic
programme.desc: In a hotel room in Paris, a doctor comes out of the shower and finds that his wife has disappeared. He soon finds himself caught up in a world of intrigue, espionage, gangsters, drugs and murder.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Murder
programme.desc: After her aunt is found dead, falling overboard on a cruise ship, Olivia's uncle's secret past is brought to life.

programme.title: Bury The Past
programme.desc: Alice was married to a deranged, abusive man: a police officer who was regarded as a pillar of the community, but was secretly a monster. After Alice killed him in self-defense, fearing her story would never be believed, she fled and went into hiding. But now an old police buddy of her dead husband is on her porch. He has tracked her down and wants money to keep silent.

programme.title: A Daughter's Nightmare
programme.desc: Following the death of her husband, Ariel's mother Dana finds a friend in the mysterious Adam. When Dana's health starts to fail, Ariel suspects Adam might not have the best of intentions.

programme.title: Black Girl Missing
programme.desc: Cheryl's daughter goes missing and is nowhere to be found. Authorities and the media dismiss her as a runaway while they focus on another missing girl, who is white.

programme.title: Deadly Secrets By the Lake
programme.desc: This whodunit murder mystery uncovers the secrets kept by the idyllic lakeside town of Thornwood Heights. It tells the story of the prodigal daughter who returns home to prove her sister's innocence of murder but is met by a lost, forbidden love, dark family secrets and a long standing family rivalry fuelled by the disappearance of a childhood best friend.

programme.title: A Chef's Deadly Revenge
programme.desc: A woman moves to a new town and opens her own gourmet restaurant after escaping from an abusive relationship. However, she soon finds herself in a deadly game of cat and mouse.

programme.title: Menendez: Blood Brothers
programme.desc: Erik and Lyle Menendez were educated, nice boys from sunny Beverly Hills, California. Erik was an exceptional tennis player and Lyle was studying at Princeton University. So when their parents were found shot dead in their home, no one could figure out why they would have done it? Everyone was perplexed. Was it for Money? For Fame? The case seemed closed, but that';s when the brothers revealed that they were sexually molested throughout their childhoods by their father, Jose. This was the trial that no one was ready for. Our story follows Erik and Lyle as they struggle with their overwhelming guilt, the harsh reality of abuse, incest and molestation that lead them down this path and the trial that shocked an entire nation of television watchers. Never before seen details emerge as we look closer into the lives of the Menendez brothers.

programme.title: Oscar Pistorius: Blade Runner Killer
programme.desc: The true story of the sprint runner dubbed theBlade Runner; and his rise to fame as a gold medalist Paralympic champion and as the first double-leg amputee to participate in the Olympics. Oscar's resilience to overcome his disability combined with his apparent fairy tale relationship with model Reeva Steenkap turned him into a media favorite. This all shattered one Valentine's Day night when four bullets were fired and Reeva's life was taken. Her brutal death shocked the world and the court room drama that followed consumed the news.

programme.title: To Have and to Hold
programme.desc: Alice, who still can't believe her high school crush, the dashing, wealthy and successful Joe, would choose to marry her, willingly allows him to mould her into his ideal socialite wife. Despite Alice's best efforts to be the woman of Joe's dreams, he can't help but be unfaithful to her. When Joe's indiscretions impact his career, Alice's life is further turned upside down. Alice unexpectedly finds herself falling for her best friend Emily's boyfriend Harry and begins to wonder if her fairy tale ending could exist after all.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' Heaven
programme.desc: Based on the novel by V.C. Andrews. Of all the poor people living in "the willies" - the foothills of the mountains of West Virginia, the Casteels were considered lowest. Yet, the eldest daughter, Heaven Leigh Casteel, was still the prettiest and smartest girl in the backwoods, despite her ragged clothes and dirty face. Heaven encouraged her four younger siblings to cling to their pride and hope for a day that they'd escape their poverty and show the world what decent, talented children they were. But when Heaven's stepmother runs away, Luke, her irresponsible drunkard of a father, decides to give away his children one by one, tearing her family apart. Heaven is sent off to live in the home of Luke's deranged ex-lover, Kitty. There, she is subjected to more torment but finds solace in the arms of her stepfather Cal, as they begin a taboo relationship.

programme.title: V.C Andrews' Ruby
programme.desc: In the heart of the bayou, Ruby Landry lives a simple, happy life. The only family Ruby Landry has ever known are her loving guardian, Grandmere Catherine, a Cajun spiritual healer, and her drunken, outcast Grandpere Jack. Her life is filled with hope and promise, especially when her attraction for handsome Paul Tate blossoms into a mysterious, wonderful love. But Paul's wealthy parents forbid him to associate with a poor Landry while Grandmere urges her to follow her dream of becoming a great painter. In a faded photograph, Ruby glimpses for the first time the image of her father and learns of a shameful deception and a shocking scheme of blackmail that now must come to light. Stunned by these revelations, she is devastated when Grandmere dies, leaving her to seek out her father in his vast New Orleans mansion. There, in a house of lies, madness, and cruel torment, Ruby clings to her memories of Paul to keep her heart alive. For only their love can save her now.

programme.title: Escaping the Madhouse: Nellie Bly Story
programme.desc: On a mission to expose the deplorable conditions and mistreatment of patients at the notorious Women's Lunatic Asylum, investigative reporter Nellie Bly feigns mental illness in order to be institutionalized to report from the inside. The movie delivers an intense and fictionalized account of actual events surrounding Nellie's stay beginning after Nellie has undergone treatment, leaving her with no recollection of how she came to the asylum or her real identity. Nellie's unwillingness to submit to authority results in unspeakable torture at the hands of the head nurse, Matron Grady. When Nellie captures the attention of Dr Josiah who tries to help her, Grady's barbaric tactics only intensify, leading Nellie to question if she actually does belong in the asylum after all. Nellie Bly's expose was the first of its kind in America and inspired the global reformation of mental health care.

programme.title: Let's Get Physical
programme.desc: Leading a double life as a fitness instructor and a prostitution ring with a client list, Sadie receives an anonymous tip and soon after her studio is raided by authorities, With only one question: who exactly was on the client list? Based on a true story.

programme.title: Man with my Husband's Face
programme.desc: When a woman's husband disappears during a kayak trip, everyone assumes that he drowned. When she catches a glimpse of a man who looks exactly like him, it sets off a chain of events.

programme.title: Zoe Gone
programme.desc: Sixteen-year-old Jennifer is already struggling with single motherhood when the kidnapping of her daughter, Zoe, kicks her maternal instincts into overdrive.

programme.title: Hoax: The Kidnapping of Sherri Papini
programme.desc: In 2016, Sherri Papini goes for a run and doesn't come home. This Northern California missing person case quickly becomes a national story when she returns and her story about being abducted doesn't add up.

programme.title: Holiday in your Heart
programme.desc: Fourteen-year-old LeAnn Rimes wants nothing more than to sing at the Grand Ole Opry. She is invited to sing at a Christmas concert on Nashville's famous stage, but upon her arrival, she is faced with the decision of leaving Nashville to be by her grandmother's bedside or to perform in the concert before returning home. Her musical inspiration, Faith Shawn, helps her to realize the importance of family.

programme.title: One Night Stand Murder
programme.desc: Alyssa wakes up in a home that's not hers and discovers a dead body. With no memory of how she got there and no idea of who the body belongs to, Alyssa tries to piece together what happened the night before.

programme.title: Revenge For My Mother
programme.desc: Audrey teaches postnatal fitness to a group of mums who bring their baby strollers to the park, but when her recently-hired assistant secretly starts exacting revenge, Audrey's perfect world erupts into madness.

programme.title: A Very Merry Toy Store
programme.desc: Two rival toy shop owners reluctantly join forces when an unscrupulous toy magnate opens a box store in their town.

programme.title: Smart Home Killer
programme.desc: After surviving an attack, a mother moves with her daughter into a smart house. As strange glitches and events occur, she realizes she's not the only one watching through security cameras.

programme.title: Finding Mrs. Claus
programme.desc: When Santa becomes too depressed to pull off Christmas after a frustrated Mrs Claus walks out on him, Santa's elves believe a little rest and relaxation will help get the big guy back on track. However, instead of taking him on a relaxing holiday, they take him to a place where the concentration of naughty people is off the charts - Las Vegas. As Santa navigates all that Vegas has to offer, which includes a Santa convention, he crosses paths with a struggling single mum and her daughter who remind him that Christmas just wouldn't be the same without him.

programme.title: Murdaugh Murders: Part 1
programme.desc: Alex Murdoch's family's hidden crimes begin piling up as he attempts to conceal his own financial felonies but falls into a dark spiral.

programme.title: Cheerleader Nightmare
programme.desc: When her cheating boyfriend is accused of murdering the head cheerleader, Sophie becomes involved in a race to discover the truth before it's too late.

programme.title: Expecting Amish
programme.desc: When an eventful Rumspringa leads to an unintended pregnancy, Amish teen Hannah must choose between returning to faith and family or beginning a new life elsewhere.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' Gates Of Paradise
programme.desc: Based on the novel Gates of Paradise, the fourth book in the "Casteel" family series by V.C. Andrews. The car crash that killed Heaven and Logan left Annie Casteel Stonewall orphaned and crippled. Whisked off to Farthinggale Manor by the possessive Tony Tatterton, Annie pines for her lost family, but especially for Luke, her half-brother. Friend of her childhood, her fantasy prince, her loving confidante without the warm glow of Luke's love, she is lost in the shadows of despair. When Annie discovers Troy's cottage hidden in Farthinggale's woods, the mystery of her past deepens. And even as she yearns to see Luke again, her hopes and dreams are darkened by the sinister Casteel spell. Treacherous, powerful and evil!

programme.title: The Night Stalker
programme.desc: Known to many as the "Night Stalker", Richard Ramirez was a cruel and prolific serial killer who murdered 14 people and terrorized Los Angeles in the summer of 1985. This film tells the story of Kit (Bellamy Young), an attorney who travels to San Quentin on an impossible mission to clear the name of Harrison Johnson (Hawthorne James), a death row inmate in Texas whom she believes has been wrongly accused of murders perpetrated by Ramirez (Lou Diamond Phillips). Kit lived in Los Angeles during the fear-tinged summer where Ramirez terrified its citizens and confronting him dredges up old and frightening memories of her own past. As the days count down to the Texas man's execution, Kit confronts Ramirez about his unspeakable crimes in search of an elusive confession, plunging into intense psychological depths in her quest for the truth.

programme.title: Big Driver
programme.desc: A mystery writer stranded on a stretch of New England road is offered assistance by another driver. She quickly discovers her saviour is actually her assailant - and a killer. From best-selling author Stephen King.

programme.title: Husband, Wife and Their Lover
programme.desc: When an Ad Exec's husband suggests a third in their bed to spice up the marriage, she invites her female trainer to join them but soon after discovers the trainer is unhinged, bent on revenge for something in the past, and must find a way to stop the woman before she ruins both their lives.

programme.title: Stalkers
programme.desc: Frustrated with the judicial system's indifference towards stalking cases, ambitious A.D.A Julia Winston is determined to establish a task force charged with tracking and prosecuting predators before they harm or kill their victims. However, Julia's boys club of bosses dismisses her concerns as trivial and repeatedly rebuffs her efforts.

programme.title: Murder at the Country Club
programme.desc: An assistant manager finds her life in danger when she uncovers corrupt activities at a prestigious country club.

programme.title: Surviving The Sleepover
programme.desc: Outspoken teenager Hannah goes to a sleepover at a popular girl's house, not realising she was only invited to be the victim of a prank.

programme.title: Nightmare School Moms
programme.desc: Two mothers battle to see which of their overachieving daughters will be accepted to a prestigious university. However, when one of their methods quickly spirals out of control, the games turn deadly.

programme.title: Finding Mrs. Claus
programme.desc: When Santa becomes too depressed to pull off Christmas after a frustrated Mrs Claus walks out on him, Santa's elves believe a little rest and relaxation will help get the big guy back on track. However, instead of taking him on a relaxing holiday, they take him to a place where the concentration of naughty people is off the charts - Las Vegas. As Santa navigates all that Vegas has to offer, which includes a Santa convention, he crosses paths with a struggling single mum and her daughter who remind him that Christmas just wouldn't be the same without him.

programme.title: My Child has My Doctor's Face
programme.desc: Jessica discovers that his biological father is actually her fertility doctor, she teams up with another one of the doctor's clients to bring him to justice.

programme.title: A Killer Among Us
programme.desc: After the shocking murder of her mother, a girl helps an unorthodox police detective with his investigation by searching her home for clues to crack the case.

programme.title: Her Affair to Die For
programme.desc: A young woman's dad becomes the obsession of her seductive roommate, who will stop at nothing to possess him.

programme.title: Once Upon a Main Street
programme.desc: Amelia, who wants to open a year-round Christmas store, bids for a shop lot against Vic, who wants to open a chocolate shop. Rivalry becomes romance when they must work together.

programme.title: Murdaugh Murders: Part 2
programme.desc: Police rush to the Murdaugh home after Alex Murdaugh reports his wife, Maggie, and son Paul dead. With police and press digging into Alex's life for leads, he attempts to derail their investigation.

programme.title: From Straight A's to XXX
programme.desc: Based on the true story of Duke University student Miriam Weeks, also known as Belle Knox. From Straight A's to XXX tells the true story of Miriam Weeks, who as a freshman at Duke University looking to make money to cover tuition, became infamously known for starring in online pornography under the pseudonym, Belle Knox. The Miriam Weeks/ Belle Knox story represents the hypocrisy of "slut-shaming". Portrayed as neither a villain nor a hero, Belle Knox is a young woman who made a choice that changed her life forever.

programme.title: Waking Up To Danger
programme.desc: A young mother picks up the pieces after a horrible accident damages her memory. She soon suspects her husband's indiscretions are what caused her suffering and that her family is in danger.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' Dark Angel
programme.desc: Based on the novel Dark Angel, the second book in the "Casteel" family series by V.C. Andrews. In her grandmother's fine, rich, Boston house, Heaven Casteel dreams of a wonderful new life of new friends, the best schools, beautiful clothes and most importantly, love. The pearls of culture, wisdom and breeding will now be hers. Soon she will make the Casteel name respectable, find her brothers and sisters and have a family again. But even in the world of the wealthy, there are strange forebodings, secrets best forgotten. And as Heaven reaches out for love, she is slowly ensnared in a sinister web of cruel deceits and hidden passions.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' Web of Dreams
programme.desc: Based on the fifth and final novel of the Casteel series the prequel, "Web of Dreams "finally unlocks the mysteries of the family. Heaven's mother Leigh had to escape from Farthinggale Manor and the secrets she harboured. Falling into the arms of Luke Casteel Sr, his devotion promised her hope as only Luke knew her deepest of secrets. Bravely she bore the suspicions of the hill folk, as she tried to grasp the happiness that long eluded her. With a baby girl, Heaven, on the way, she hoped for a chance at happy ever after.

programme.title: Britney Ever After
programme.desc: This is the tumultuous true story of Britney Jean Spears, one of the bestselling teenage music artists of all-time, whose dating life and public emotional breakdowns were the subjects of a worldwide media frenzy. By the age of 21, Britney Spears already had a number one platinum, debut album, a cover on Rolling Stone, a record-breaking second album, and international superstardom. Success in her personal life, however, would be much harder to achieve. A well-publicized romance and break-up with Justin Timberlake, a three-day marriage to a childhood sweetheart, and an ill-fated marriage to back-up dancer Kevin Federline made for a chaotic contrast to her record-setting music career.

programme.title: My Nightmare Office Affair
programme.desc: Nick is a successful executive with a picture-perfect family, loving wife and adorable daughter. It looks like he has it all to his boss, Lisa, who desperately wants a child of her own. Lisa seduces Nick in his moment of weakness, hoping to remove his wife from the picture so she can fill her role as wife and mother. When Nick tries to break things off with Lisa, he finds himself in a dangerous game with her that threatens his job, his family and his life.

programme.title: The Venice Murders
programme.desc: When her new roommate goes missing in Italy, an art student teams up with her eccentric aunt to save her friend and bring the kidnapper to justice.

programme.title: Watch Your Back
programme.desc: A woman and her husband become increasingly scared as an anonymous person begins stalking their family.

programme.title: V.C Andrews' Pearl In The Mist
programme.desc: Fate whisked Ruby from a simple life in the Louisiana Bayou. But her new riches bring more treachery than happiness. Even after a year as a Dumas, Ruby still wonders at the splendor of the family's New Orleans mansion and rejoices in the love of the father she had never known. But true happiness in her new home is as elusive as the swamp mist. Ruby must carefully avoid her venomous stepmother, Daphne, while making every effort to befriend her twin sister, Gisselle. While attending Greenwood, the exclusive girls' boarding school, Ruby doesn't lose hope in a world that never really wanted her. Ruby will have to summon every last ounce of her Cajun strength to reclaim her home, her future, and the happiness she once knew.

programme.title: FOX SPORTS News
programme.desc: The latest highlights, reaction and analysis of the biggest sport stories from Australia and around the world.

programme.desc: Putting the "personal" in personal finance, get an inside look at the lives and finances of millennials. See exactly how much they earn, what they spend it on and how they invest. From starting a business to changing careers, getting in and out of debt, creating an unusual income stream, or casting it all aside to start over again young people reveal the steps they took to make it happen. Including how much they get paid, what they spend on food, shelter and fun, and how thy plan on saving for the future, Millennial Money takes a revealing look into the one area people seem to never talk about: their money.

programme.title: American Greed
programme.sub-title: Ep 187: The Trials of Michael Avenatti
programme.desc: "American Greed" goes inside the dark side of the American Dream - where money seduces, power corrupts, and smooth criminals will stop at nothing to get rich. Their complex scams leave victim's lives in shambles. Each episode is a deep dive into the minds and actions of heartless crooks who live lives most people can only dream of. But how many luxury homes and exotic cars does it take to justify these white collar crimes? Ultimately for the crooks the dream turns into a nightmare when their shady plans unravel. "American Greed" follows the money through the eyes of the criminals, the victims, and the investigators who bring these scammers to justice.
